explanation: Agent A is correct. The default: break; in the switch is actually executed (log shows the default branch taken for idtype==0) and performs no action or side-effect. Per MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2 an executed operation whose removal would not affect program behaviour is dead code. Removing the default label and its break would not change control flow or program behaviour for the observed cases, so this executed no-op meets the rule's definition of dead code.
